	<br>						
	
	<h2>Policy Update: Premium Transportation as Part of an Approved Accommodation</h2>
	
	
	
	
	
	
	<span class="strongText">2/25/2020 
	</span>
	
	
		<p><!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01//EN"
                      "http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/strict.dtd">
<p>The Office of the Vice President and Comptroller announces
  adjustments to policies and procedures regarding the purchase of
  premium transportation as part of an approved accommodation. This
  change was previously announced on <a
    href="https://apps.obfs.uillinois.edu/news/dsp_News.cfm?FY=2020&A=1A7A25F6-9E85-4374-8262-39F80063A159">December
    19, 2019</a>.Â Effective March 1, 2020, persons seeking to purchase
  premium transportation as part of an approved accommodation must
  obtain written authorization from the appropriate university equal
  employment opportunity (EEO) office prior to purchase. This approval
  must be submitted with any related expense reports. Units should no
  longer attach medical or other health-related records to expense reports.</p>
<p>Updated policy and procedural information will be published in
  sections <a
    href="https://www.obfs.uillinois.edu/bfpp/section-8-payments-reimbursements/request-reimbursement-travel-business-meals">8.2.1
    Request Reimbursement for Domestic or International Employee Travel
    and Business Meals</a> and <a
    href="https://www.obfs.uillinois.edu/bfpp/section-15-travel/make-travel-arrangements">15.1.3
    Make Travel Arrangements</a> of the Business and Financial Policies
  and Procedures Manual.</p>
<p>
  <strong>Contact</strong>
  <br> For questions about requesting authorization to purchase premium
  transportation as part of an approved accommodation contact your
  university equal employment opportunity (EEO) office.</p>
<p>
  <strong>University of Illinois at Chicago</strong>
  <br> Office for Access and Equity<br> Phone: (312) 996-8670<br> Email:
    <a href="mailto:oae@uic.edu">oae@uic.edu</a><br>
  <a
    href="https://oae.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/32/2017/05/reasonableAccomodationMedicalConditionForm_OAE.pdf">UIC
    Employee Request for Reasonable Accommodation Based on Medical Condition</a>
</p>
<p>
  <strong>University of Illinois at Springfield</strong>
  <br> Human Resources Office<br> Phone: (217) 206-7237<br> Email: <a href="mailto:alozz2@uis.edu">alozz2@uis.edu</a></p>
<p>
  <strong>University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign</strong>
  <br> Office for Access and Equity<br> Phone: (217) 333-0885<br> Email:
    <a href="mailto:accessandequity@illinois.edu">accessandequity@illinois.edu</a><br>
  <a
    href="https://illinois-accommodate.symplicity.com/public_accommodation/">Online
    Employee Accommodation Request</a>
</p>
<p>
  <strong>University of Illinois System (System Office Employees)</strong>
  <br> System Human Resource Services<br> Phone: (217) 333-2600<br>
  Email: <a href="mailto:lacyjk@uillinois.edu">lacyjk@uillinois.edu</a><br>
  <a
    href="https://www.hr.uillinois.edu/system_office_employees/system_office_forms/reasonable_accommodation">Reasonable
    Accommodation Medical Condition Form</a>
</p>
<p>
  <br> For questions about the Business and Financial Policies and
  Procedures Manual, contact the Office of Business Services at <a
  href="mailto:obfspolicies@uillinois.edu">obfspolicies@uillinois.edu</a>
  or (312) 585-9049.</p></p>
	
